UNITED STATES of America, v. Joseph L. ZERBONI, Administrator With the Will Annexed of the Estate of Marie Rough Zerboni, Deceased. No. 9332. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct. 9, 1939. Ben Plarrison, U. S. Atty., E. H. Mitchell, Asst. U. S. Atty., and Eugene Harpole, Sp. Atty., Bureau of Internal Revenue, all of Los Angeles, Cal. Dempsey & Mackay, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
